         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 2nd June 1877. ¶ Dear Sir ¶  ¶ Having sold to Baron Mueller the 2000 acres of Land which by Earl Carnarvon's despatch, His Excellency Governor Robinsons letter, and the decision of the Wes...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">M77.06.02</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Ernest Giles to John Forrest</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Colonial Secretary's Office</seg>, SDUR/G4/325b, State Archives, Battye Library, Perth.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">To proof.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">check loc. cit. Is this a copy? It is in the same hand as E. Giles to M, 2 June 1877.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">2nd June 1877.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Having sold to Baron Mueller the 2000 acres of Land which by Earl Carnarvon's despatch, His Excellency Governor Robinsons letter, and the decision of the West Australian Government I am entitled to select any where on Crown Lands in your Colonial territory in acknowledgement of my geographic Explorations: I beg of you to effect the selecting according to your […]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">it isn't 'kind' - p/c murky here.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> offer so to do <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as early as possible to cause the Crown Grant to be made out without delay and to adopt measures to effect at once the transfer of this property unreservedly to Baron Ferdinand von Mueller by any needful Legal Documents</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours faithfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ernest Giles<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also E. Giles to M, 2 June 1877; J. Forrest to <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Commissioner of Crown Lands</seg>, 5 September 1877.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">To John Forrest Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Deputy Surveyor General</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">—<seg style=""> </seg>Perth —<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">these three lines are in a different hand.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
